      "example_rewrite": "| **Principle** | **Meaning** |\n|---|---|\n| **Community Before Commerce** | Festival and arts partners make commitments based on trust in the mission; lead every conversation with Story Portal's community-preservation purpose before discussing revenue share or integration terms. |\n| **Asymmetric Value Design** | Story Portal is typically the smaller party; structure agreements so the partner gains visible, measurable wins in year one (e.g., expanded audience data, co-branded content) to earn reciprocal long-term access. |\n| **Relationship Continuity Over Deal Velocity** | A rejected term today does not end a partnership; document 'not yet' decisions and schedule a 6-month re-engagement so no potential partner is permanently lost. |\n| **Integration Readiness Gate** | Never commit a partner to a technical integration timeline without written confirmation from the Product Manager that the API or data feed is production-ready. |\n| **Burn Culture Fluency** | Burning Man-adjacent partners (Love Burn, regional burns) operate on gifting and participation norms; proposals must respect those values and avoid transactional language that signals commodification. |\n| **Paper Trails Protect Relationships** | Every verbal agreement, commitment, or concern raised in a partner call gets summarized in a follow-up email within 24 hours — protecting both parties and preventing drift. |"
